problem_text_en:
When a simple harmonic mechanical wave propagates in the same medium, the correct conclusion is (  )
A. When the frequencies are different, the wave speeds are different and the wavelengths are also different;
B. When the frequencies are different, the wave speeds are the same and the wavelengths are different;
C. When the frequencies are different, the wave speeds are the same and the wavelengths are also the same;
D. When the frequencies are different, the wave speeds are different and the wavelengths are the same.
